{"type":"message","id":"6eb12314","parentId":"f3f32aff","timestamp":"2026-07-12T11:13:00.465Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:496bf277-633c-4b83-8a1d-aad560dbfbb8 LinkedIn Post 3 - AI usage not coding] Publish this LinkedIn post NOW for user 264468965. Use this image: /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\n\nPost text:\n𝟵𝟭% 𝗼𝗳 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘂𝘀𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗴.\n\nNew data from 1.2 million Claude Cowork sessions:\n→ 33.4% business process and operations\n→ 16.4% content creation\n→ 8.7% software development\n\nThe dominant use case isn't writing code. It's \"the work around the work\" — status reports, slide decks, onboarding checklists, variance memos.\n\nThe stuff that every role has to do but no one's job title includes.\n\nEveryone's been optimizing for developers. Anthropic just mapped the real market: every knowledge worker with a laptop and a pile of spreadsheets.\n\nMobile and web launch this week. Schedule a task at 6 AM. Claude works through the email threads and transcripts while you sleep. Review it over coffee.\n\nThe shift: AI isn't here to do your job. It's here to do everything around your job so you can focus on the part that matters.\n\nWhat's the \"work around the work\" eating your week?\n\n#AI #Productivity #EnterpriseAI #KnowledgeWork #Automation\nCurrent time: Sunday, July 12th, 2026 - 11:13 AM (UTC)\nReference UTC: 2026-07-12 11:13 UTC\n\nReturn your response as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself."}],"timestamp":1783854780455}}
